"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711485","Department of Health","false","2017-03-23","<p>The number of incidents of physical restraint being applied to people with mental health conditions in Bradford Districts Care Trust and each trust in England for 2011/12 to 2015/16 is attached. It should be noted that not all providers submitted restraint data during this period. 2015/16 only includes figures April to November due to a change in datasets at this time.</p><p> </p><p>Data for 2010/11 is not available due to a change in dataset.</p>","Oxford West and Abingdon","Nicola Blackwood",,"2017-03-23T14:24:18.24Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711485/answer","Biography information for Baroness Blackwood of North Oxford","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711485/answer","PQ68069 attached document.xlsx","PQ68069 attached document.xlsx","PQ68069 attached table","PQ68069 attached table","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711485/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-15","Mental Health Services: Restraint Techniques","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, how many incidents there were of physical restraint being applied to people with mental health conditions in (a) Bradford Districts Care Trust and (b) each trust in England in each year since 2010.","false","Biography information for Imran Hussain","Bradford East","Imran Hussain","68069"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711486","Department of Health","false","2017-03-24","<p>FOI statistics are Official Statistics and are governed by the standards set out by the UK Statistics Authority (UKSA) in their Code of Practice. To publish information outside of the release timetable would be a breach of Protocol 2 of the Code of Practice for Official Statistics.</p><p> </p><p>The latest Freedom of Information statistics were published in December 2016 and are available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/freedom-of-information-statistics-july-to-september-2016--2" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/statistics/freedom-of-information-statistics-july-to-september-2016--2</a></p>","Warrington South","David Mowat",,"2017-03-24T12:31:57.05Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711486/answer","Biography information for David Mowat","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711486/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711486/answer",,,,,"17","Health","Health","2017-03-15","Department of Health: Freedom of Information","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Health, what the average response rate was of his Department to individual Freedom of Information requests in each month since July 2016.","false","Biography information for Andrew Gwynne","Denton and Reddish","Andrew Gwynne","68045"
