"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/710906","Cabinet Office","false","2017-03-20","<p>The Department’s records are maintained in accordance with the Public Records Act 1958. The Department is also implementing the recommendations of Sir Alex Allan’s Review of Government Digital Records and the Better Information for Better Government report, available at:</p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/government-digital-records-and-archives-review-by-sir-alex-allan" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/government-digital-records-and-archives-review-by-sir-alex-allan</a></p><p> </p><p><a href="https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/better-information-for-better-government" target="_blank">https://www.gov.uk/government/publications/better-information-for-better-government</a></p>","Ipswich","Ben Gummer",,"2017-03-20T12:14:30.65Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/710906/answer","Biography information for Ben Gummer","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/710906/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/710906/answer",,,,,"53","Cabinet Office","Cabinet Office","2017-03-14","Cabinet Office: Databases","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for the Cabinet Office, what assessment he has made of the adequacy of his Department's records management system.","false","Biography information for Tom Watson","West Bromwich East","Tom Watson","67901"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/710907","HM Treasury","false","2017-03-22","<p>The earlier reported number of 89 has been corrected (separately) to reflect 86 civil servants managing external contracts.</p><p> </p><p>The pay grades of the civil servants referred to in the response of 2 March 2017 range from Range C (Executive Officer equivalent) to Range F (Senior Civil Servant Pay Band 1 equivalent), please see the table below with the breakdown.</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td><p><strong>Range</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>Volume</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p>C</p></td><td><p>4</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>D</p></td><td><p>34</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>E</p></td><td><p>43</p></td></tr><tr><td><p>F</p></td><td><p>5</p></td></tr></tbody></table>","Brighton, Kemptown","Simon Kirby",,"2017-03-22T11:27:30.53Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/710907/answer","Biography information for Simon Kirby","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/710907/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/710907/answer",,,,,"14","Treasury","CaTreasury","2017-03-14","Treasury: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask Mr Chancellor of the Exchequer, pursuant to the Answer of 2 March 2017 to Question 65005, what the pay grades are of the 89 civil servants of his Department who manage external contracts.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","67885"
