employed in the Commercial and Contract Management Directorate are employed; on what pay grades the 100 contract employed by the Legal Aid Agency are employed; and on what pay grades the 218 are employed by the National Offender Management Service employed.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","67851"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711067","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-21","<p>In 2015-16, 1,405 band 3-5 prison officers took sickness absence due to mental and behavioural disorders. In accordance with the Data Protection Act, figures on the length of each sickness absence cannot be published.</p><p> </p><p>NOMS is committed to providing safe, decent and secure places of work and takes the health, safety and wellbeing of its employees extremely seriously. The Ministry of Justice is investing an extra £100m annually to boost the frontline by 2,500 officers.</p><p> </p><p>NOMS also recognises that the physical, emotional and social wellbeing of employees is paramount to attracting and retaining staff that will build a strong and capable organisation. All NOMS staff have access to an occupational health service and employee assistance programme. This includes 24 hour, 365 days a year access to signposting and counselling; trauma support services; a wide ranging health promotion website and personal wellbeing zone.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, counselling is available to staff who have experienced trauma. Fast track referrals to see an occupational health nurse are encouraged for staff who have experienced trauma and, where staff are absent as a result of a mental and behavioural disorder, an immediate referral to occupational health is recommended.</p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-03-21T11:44:53.767Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711067/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711067/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711067/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-03-14","Prison Officers: Mental Illness","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many prison officers were on leave of absence due to mental illness in 2015-16; and for how many days each such absence lasted.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","67892"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711068","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-20","<p>Custody suites were closed in six courts during the 2015-16 financial year. Five of these closures were as a consequence of the closure of the courthouse.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-03-20T15:12:14.37Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711068/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711068/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711068/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-03-14","Police Custody: Courts","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many custody suites in courts were closed in 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","67895"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711069","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-21","<p>There are no plans to issue a pro forma for courts in England and Wales to assist with the precise wording of restraining orders. The terms in which court orders are made is a matter for the court and the prohibitions imposed by a restraining order will depend to a significant extent on the circumstances of the individual case.</p>","North East Hertfordshire","Sir Oliver Heald",,"2017-03-21T12:05:57.337Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711069/answer","Biography information for Sir Oliver Heald","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711069/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711069/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-03-14","Restraining Orders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, whether her Department plans to issue a pro forma for courts in England and Wales to assist with the precise wording of restraining orders.","false","Biography information for Jess Phillips","Birmingham, Yardley","Jess Phillips","67915"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711070","Department for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","false","2017-03-21","<p>The maximum penalties for animal welfare offences are kept under regular review. The Sentencing Council has very recently published revised magistrate’s court sentencing guidelines, including those in relation to animal welfare offences, which include dog fighting, with the aim of ensuring that the most serious cases of animal cruelty receive appropriately severe penalties within the available maximum penalty.</p><p> </p>","Camborne and Redruth","George Eustice",,"2017-03-21T12:24:18.607Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711070/answer","Biography information for George Eustice","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711070/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711070/answer",,,,,"13","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","Environment, Food and Rural Affairs","2017-03-14","Dog Fighting","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Environment, Food and Rural Affairs, what plans her Department has to increase the maximum penalty for dog fighting.","false","Biography information for Julian Knight","Solihull","Julian Knight","67928"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711071","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-20","<p>A Serious Further Offence (SFO) review is undertaken where an offender under statutory supervision in the community is charged with a qualifying offence. Not every offender charged with an SFO will eventually be convicted of an SFO.</p><p> </p><p>The table below provides a breakdown of the figures of the Serious Further Offence Reviews (SFO) Reviews that were completed following investigations undertaken by a) the National Probation Service (NPS) and b) Community Rehabilitation Companies (CRCs) in England and Wales since February 2015</p><p> </p><table><tbody><tr><td rowspan="2"><p><strong> </strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>England</strong></p></td><td colspan="2"><p><strong>Wales</strong></p></td><td rowspan="2"><p><strong>Total</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>NPS</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>CRC</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>NPS</strong></p></td><td><p><strong>CRC</strong></p></td></tr><tr><td><p><strong>1 February 2015 </strong> <strong>– 31 January 2017</strong></p></td><td><p>529</p></td><td><p>435</p></td><td><p>33</p></td><td><p>24</p></td><td><p>1021</p></td></tr></tbody></table><p> </p>","East Surrey","Mr Sam Gyimah",,"2017-03-20T10:45:28.733Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711071/answer","Biography information for Mr Sam Gyimah","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711071/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711071/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-03-14","Reoffenders","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many Serious Further Offence reviews involving (a) the National Probation Service and (b) Community Rehabilitation companies in England and Wales have been conducted since February 2015.","false","Biography information for Liz Saville Roberts","Dwyfor Meirionnydd","Liz Saville Roberts","67914"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711072","Ministry of Justice","false","2017-03-23","<p>The information requested could only be obtained at disproportionate cost</p><p> </p><p>The MOJ is working with the Government Commercial Function to capture such data going forward as part of our investment in the development of our risk and controls framework.</p>","Bracknell","Dr Phillip Lee",,"2017-03-23T14:20:09.51Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711072/answer","Biography information for Dr Phillip Lee","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711072/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711072/answer",,,,,"54","Justice","Justice","2017-03-14","Ministry of Justice: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Justice, how many contracts procured by her Department and its arms-length bodies require that the contractor pays those of its employees undertaking the work contracted for the real living wage as defined by the Living Wage Foundation in each of the last three financial years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","67774"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711073","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-03-20","<p>The Secretary of State meets regularly with Cabinet colleagues, to discuss issues that directly affect security in Northern Ireland.</p><p>In Northern Ireland, Ammunition Technical Officers (ATO) are deployed at the request of the PSNI.</p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2017-03-20T17:32:14.057Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711073/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711073/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711073/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-03-14","Bomb Disposal: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, if he will hold discussions with the Secretary of State for Defence on the most efficient use of the deployment of army bomb disposal units, particularly when dealing with numerous incidents in the West and North West of Northern Ireland.","false","Biography information for Mr Gregory Campbell","East Londonderry","Mr Gregory Campbell","67789"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711074","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-03-16","<p>The Secretary of State wrote to the Northern Ireland parties in January to seek their views on moving to full transparency. The Government is keen to make progress on this issue following the recent Assembly election.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","67844","2017-03-16T15:49:50.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711074/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711074/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711074/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-03-14","Political Parties: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what steps he is taking to accelerate the introduction of legislation to provide transparency in relation to donations to all political parties operating in Northern Ireland; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","67843"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711075","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-03-21","<p>The pay grades of the 10 civil servants in the Department who oversee contracts which have been awarded to external providers are:</p><p>4 Band As;</p><p>2 Band Bs;</p><p>3 Band Cs; and</p><p>1 Band D.</p><p> </p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2017-03-21T15:41:43.647Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711075/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711075/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711075/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-03-14","Northern Ireland Office: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, pursuant to the Answer of 1 March 2017 to Question 65004, what the pay grades are of the 10 civil servants of his Department who oversee contracts awarded to external providers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","67884"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711076","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-03-21","<p>As set out in the Government’s White Paper, <em>The United Kingdom’s exit from, and new partnership with, the European Union</em>, the Government’s guiding principle is to ensure that as the UK leaves the EU, no new barriers to living and doing business within the Union are created. We will work with the devolved administrations on an approach to returning powers from the EU that works for the whole of the UK.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2017-03-21T15:43:26.733Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711076/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711076/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711076/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-03-14","Northern Ireland Assembly: Powers","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what steps he is taking to ensure the devolution of additional powers to the Northern Ireland Assembly after the UK leaves the EU; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","67845"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711077","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-03-16","<p>The Secretary of State wrote to the Northern Ireland parties in January to seek their views on moving to full transparency. The Government is keen to make progress on this issue following the recent Assembly election.</p><p><strong> </strong></p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins","67843","2017-03-16T15:49:50.193Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711077/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711077/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711077/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-03-14","Political Parties: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, what recent assessment he has made of the risks of removing the anonymity of donors to political parties operating in Northern Ireland; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","67844"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711078","Northern Ireland Office","false","2017-03-21","<p>Under the Syrian Vulnerable Persons Resettlement scheme, 309 Syrian refugees were resettled to Northern Ireland in 2016.</p><p> </p><p>Unaccompanied asylum seeking and refugee children are supported by the relevant authorities in England, Scotland, Wales and Northern Ireland and in accordance with their respective children’s legislation. In July last year the Government introduced the National Transfer Scheme (NTS) to ensure there is a more even distribution of caring responsibilities for unaccompanied asylum seeking and refugee children across the country.</p><p> </p><p>The Home Office are working to extend the transfer provisions in the Immigration Act 2016 to the devolved administrations. Building upon Northern Ireland's positive contribution to the Syrian Vulnerable Persons Resettlement scheme, the Home Office continues to be in contact with the Northern Ireland Executive regarding unaccompanied asylum seeking children. We remain open to any offers of NTS places from the relevant authorities in the devolved administrations however, no unaccompanied asylum-seeking children have been resettled in Northern Ireland under section 67 of the Immigration Act 2016 yet.</p><p> </p>","Keighley","Kris Hopkins",,"2017-03-21T15:45:47.427Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711078/answer","Biography information for Kris Hopkins","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711078/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711078/answer",,,,,"21","Northern Ireland","Northern Ireland","2017-03-14","Asylum: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Northern Ireland, how many (a) refugees from Syria and (b) unaccompanied refugee children from Europe have been settled in Northern Ireland in the last year; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","67846"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711079","Prime Minister","false","2017-03-22","<p>I visit all parts of the United Kingdom regularly. Details of my visits within the United Kingdom are published on the <a href="http://gov.uk/" target="_blank">gov.uk</a> website.</p>","Maidenhead","Mrs Theresa May",,"2017-03-22T13:46:57.92Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711079/answer","Biography information for Mrs Theresa May","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711079/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711079/answer",,,,,"23","Prime Minister","Prime Minister","2017-03-14","Domestic Visits: Northern Ireland","1","House of Commons","To ask the Prime Minister, when she next plans to visit Northern Ireland; and if she will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Lady Hermon","North Down","Lady Hermon","67842"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711080","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-21","<p>In 2016 the Department asked Local Authorities to apply for Bikeability funding. 107 Local Authorities applied and every authority was awarded grant funding.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-03-21T14:15:26.913Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711080/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711080/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711080/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Cycling: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many local authorities have applied for Bikeability funding since 2015; and how  many of those applications were successful.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","67838"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711081","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-22","<p /><p /><p /><p /><table><tbody><tr><td><p /></td><td><p /></td></tr><tr><td><p /></td><td><p /></td></tr><tr><td><p /></td><td><p /></td></tr><tr><td><p /></td><td><p /></td></tr><tr><td><p /></td><td><p /></td></tr><tr><td><p /></td><td><p /></td></tr></tbody></table><p>The Government believes that people have the right to a higher wage and not to be punished by higher taxes. As part of this, from April 2016, we introduced a new mandatory National Living Wage (NLW) for workers aged 25 and above, and this will rise to £7.50 an hour in April 2017. DfT contractors are required to comply with all legal requirements, including payment of the National Minimum Wage and the National Living Wage as applicable. My Department does not have central records to the level of detail as to whether any given contract pays a higher rate.</p><p> </p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-03-22T10:48:01.393Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711081/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711081/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711081/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Department for Transport: Procurement","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many contracts procured by his Department and its arms-length bodies require that the contractor pays those of its employees undertaking the work contracted the real living wage as defined by the Living Wage Foundation in each of the last three financial years.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","67775"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711082","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-20","<p>Following contract award, the Main Works contractors will be in place later this year. As designs mature, the programme of works will be developed, culminating in a detailed programme being available by the end of 2018.</p><p> </p><p>Programmes are currently being developed for individual localised Enabling Works packages such as habitat creations, site clearance and highway improvements in preparation for the Main Works. HS2 Ltd will be meeting my Right Hon. Friend on 27 March to provide an update on the works within the Chiltern area and the process for developing the programme.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-03-20T12:07:09.323Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711082/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711082/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711082/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","High Speed 2 Railway Line: Chilterns","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, when HS2 Ltd plans to provide the detailed programme of works for the Chilterns.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","67792"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711083","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-21","<p>Industry expert Chris Gibb has provided advice to the department on Southern Rail. His recommendations, which are technical in nature, and the Government’s response will be published in due course.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-03-21T12:02:43.71Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711083/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711083/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711083/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Southern: Standards","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer to Question 60337, on Southern: standards, when the full report and recommendations of Chris Gibb's project board into rapid improvements of Southern Rail will be published.","false","Biography information for Peter Kyle","Hove","Peter Kyle","67853"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711084","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-21","<p>The Secretary of State has no such plans.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-03-21T11:57:46.017Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711084/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711084/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711084/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Railway Stations: Greater London","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, whether he plans to designate stations outside the current Greater London boundary as Greater London Stations for the purposes of possible inclusion in the services devolved to Transport for London.","false","Biography information for Kwasi  Kwarteng","Spelthorne","Kwasi Kwarteng","67835"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711085","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-22","<p>The pay grades of the 679 civil servants of my Department, who oversee contracts awarded to external providers, range from Executive Officer or equivalent to Senior Civil Servant or equivalent.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-03-22T11:32:17.053Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711085/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711085/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711085/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Department for Transport: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, pursuant to the Answer of 28 February 2017 to Question 65407, what the pay grades are of the 679 civil servants of his Department who oversee contracts awarded to external providers.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","67883"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711086","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-22","<p>On 9 March, the Department announced that it would provide a £625,000 funding contribution to the England’s Economic Heartland Strategic Alliance (EEH). This will enable EEH to support the Government’s aspirations for the Cambridge to Milton Keynes to Oxford corridor. It will do this by providing a clear evidence base to support transport investment decisions in the region, and by helping to ensure that transport infrastructure improvements facilitate economic and housing growth.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-03-22T10:43:33.9Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711086/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711086/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711086/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Transport: South East","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what support his Department is providing for the work of the England's Economic Heartland Strategic Alliance to improve rail and road links across the area.","false","Biography information for Dame Cheryl Gillan","Chesham and Amersham","Mrs Cheryl Gillan","67890"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711087","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-20","<p>The Secretary of State has made no recent assessment of the capacity of Swindon station.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-03-20T15:03:57.463Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711087/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711087/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711087/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Railway Stations: Swindon","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what recent assessment he has made of the capacity of Swindon station.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","67922"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711088","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-23","<p>We have not made any assessment of the demand for new tyres for vehicles constructed or first registered before 1960. We have the following figures for personal injury accidents where at least one of the vehicles involved was constructed or first registered before 1960:</p><p> </p><p>2012: 55</p><p>2013: 51</p><p>2014: 54</p><p>2015: 45</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-03-23T10:25:19.677Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711088/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711088/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711088/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Motor Vehicles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the decline in demand for new tyres for pre-1960 vehicles since the requirement for an annual MOT test for such vehicles was removed in 2012; whether there has been an increase in the number of road traffic accidents involving such vehicles since 2012; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","67981"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711089","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-23","<p>The MOT test is an effective tool for checking annually that vehicles meet minimum roadworthiness standards, including those applying to the condition of tyres. Of the around 27 million registered cars eligible for MOT, 7,789,251 class 3 and 4 vehicles (cars, vans and passenger vehicles with up to 12 seats) failed the MOT during the business year 2015/2016. A total of 599,772 (7.7%) of those test failures related to defective tyres. Identification of tyre-related defects at MOT prevented the cars to which they were fitted from being used on public roads with unroadworthy tyres.</p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-03-23T10:16:44.09Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711089/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711089/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711089/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Motor Vehicles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effectiveness of MOT testing in ensuring that vehicles with unroadworthy tyres are not used on the public highway.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","67980"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711090","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-23","<p>From 16 September to 2 November 2016 we consulted over proposals to implement European Directive 2014/45 on periodic tests for roadworthiness. The Directive provided that Member States could exempt vehicles over 30 years old, provided they had not been substantially changed. Our proposals were developed following an informal consultation in 2014.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-03-23T10:35:28.27Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711090/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711090/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711090/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Motor Vehicles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what role the EU had in promoting the exemption of 40 year-old cars from MOT inspections; and if he will make a statement.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","67983"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711091","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-20","<p>Station usage statistics are collected and published by the Office of Rail and Road. The usage of Swindon station shown in those statistics is:</p><p> </p><p>2000-01: 2,064,669</p><p>2001-02: 2,011,159</p><p>2002-03: 2,117,084</p><p>2003-04: -*</p><p>2004-05: 2,257,719</p><p>2005-06: 2,340,952</p><p>2006-07: 2,515,492</p><p>2007-08: 2,758,891</p><p>2008-09: 2,905,266</p><p>2009-10: 2,835,364</p><p>2010-11: 3,039,228</p><p>2011-12: 3,232,578</p><p>2012-13: 3,220,180</p><p>2013-14: 3,350,444</p><p>2014-15: 3,503,982</p><p>2015-16: 3,580,540</p><p> </p><p>* The statistics consistently omit the 2003-04 year due to a change in the statistical series.</p><p> </p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-03-20T15:12:55.943Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711091/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711091/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711091/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Railway Stations: Swindon","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, how many people used Swindon station in each year since 2000.","false","Biography information for Justin Tomlinson","North Swindon","Justin Tomlinson","67908"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711092","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-17","<p>The Department recognises that Pacers fall short of passengers’ expectations and so required bidders for the Northern franchise to phase them out.</p><p> </p><p>Arriva Rail North are investing £400 million in 281 brand new air-conditioned carriages, more than double the minimum required in the government’s invitation to tender, and remain on track to deliver the complete removal of the outdated and unpopular Pacers by the end of 2019 at the latest.</p>","Blackpool North and Cleveleys","Paul Maynard",,"2017-03-17T09:59:54.67Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711092/answer","Biography information for Paul Maynard","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711092/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711092/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Rolling Stock: North of England","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what progress his Department is making in replacing pacer trains.","false","Biography information for Andrew Stephenson","Pendle","Andrew Stephenson","67940"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711093","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-21","<p>Bikeability Plus has been developed to address specific barriers to children cycling more often, in addition to and support of the core Bikeability training. It was piloted in a number of areas across England. During the pilot, the number of children who cycled to school at least once a week more than doubled. During the piloting of Bikeability Plus, a number of authorities reported positive impacts on the provision of core Bikeability training. It was found that in areas where Bikeability Plus had been delivered, instructors delivering core Bikeability modules were able to spend more time on the road training children. Monitoring of Bikeability and Bikeability Plus programmes is ongoing.</p><p> </p>","Harrogate and Knaresborough","Andrew Jones",,"2017-03-21T14:18:17.983Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711093/answer","Biography information for Andrew Jones","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711093/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711093/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Cycling: Finance","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the effect of using Bikeability funding to deliver Bikeability Plus on the provision of Bikeability training.","false","Biography information for Daniel Zeichner","Cambridge","Daniel Zeichner","67941"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711094","Department for Transport","false","2017-03-23","<p>From 16 September to 2 November 2016 we consulted over proposals to exempt vehicles from annual roadworthiness tests. The consultation document included an Impact Assessment, which estimated the risks to road users of the options in the consultation.</p><p> </p><p>We expect to announce a decision on the outcome of the consultation soon.</p>","South Holland and The Deepings","Mr John Hayes",,"2017-03-23T10:31:49.877Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711094/answer","Biography information for Sir John Hayes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711094/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711094/answer",,,,,"27","Transport","Transport","2017-03-14","Motor Vehicles: Testing","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Transport, what assessment he has made of the increased risk to road-users consequent on any future decision to exempt from MOT tests any vehicle built more than 40 years ago; and when the consultation on that proposal is due to report.","false","Biography information for Dr Julian Lewis","New Forest East","Dr Julian Lewis","67982"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711095","Women and Equalities","false","2017-03-20","<p>The Government Equalities Office does not currently intend to use HMRC data to help identify non-compliant employers. The regulations introducing mandatory gender pay gap reporting will require employers to publish the information on their own website and a Government website. This will allow us to monitor closely the levels of compliance, and we will keep our approach under review during the early years of implementation.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-03-20T17:41:37.897Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711095/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711095/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711095/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-03-14","Equal Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, whether her Department will have access to HM Revenue and Customs data in order to help identify non-compliant businesses once gender pay gap reporting  requirements are in place in April 2018.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","68000"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711096","Women and Equalities","false","2017-03-21","<p>The Government supports the principle of gender equality and sympathises with the concerns over gender inequality in the succession to peerages.</p><p> </p><p>However, neither a life peerage nor a hereditary peerage, as a dignity or honour conferred by the Crown, is a public or personal office for the purposes of the Equality Act 2010. As such, the Register of Hereditary Peers is not subject to equalities legislation.</p>","Gosport","Caroline Dinenage",,"2017-03-21T16:50:10.133Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711096/answer","Biography information for Caroline Dinenage","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711096/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711096/answer",,,,,"31","Women and Equalities","Women and Equalities","2017-03-14","Hereditary Peers: Gender","1","House of Commons","To ask the Minister for Women and Equalities, what discussions she has had with Cabinet colleagues on the effect of male primogeniture on the gender balance of hereditary peers in the House of Lords.","false","Biography information for Rachel Reeves","Leeds West","Rachel Reeves","67854"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711097","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-20","<p>We have systems in place to ensure that Jobcentre staff can identify customers at risk of suicide or self harm and refer them to appropriate local sources of help.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-03-20T17:34:13.24Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711097/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711097/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711097/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-03-14","Unemployed People: Mental Health","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, if he will make it his policy to ensure that every jobcentre has available information leaflets on suicide prevention.","false","Biography information for Luciana Berger","Liverpool, Wavertree","Luciana Berger","67873"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711098","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-20","<p>Throughout the development of the proposals for East Ham Jobcentre the department has been mindful of the impact on staff and customers as part of its duties under section 149 of the Equality Act 2010. Statistical analysis of the potential impact of the proposals on people with the protected characteristics has informed high-level decision-making so far. As we obtain further local, site-specific information we will ensure any issues identified are also taken fully into consideration when the final decisions are made. Existing DWP processes make provision for those unable to travel independently to their designated Jobcentre.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-03-20T17:38:57.557Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711098/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711098/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711098/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-03-14","Jobcentres: East Ham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the effect on clients with sensory and mobility impairments, and those unable to travel independently of the closure of East Ham Jobcentre Plus.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","67871"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711099","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-20","<p>Throughout the development of these proposals, the department has been mindful of the impact on staff and customers as part of its duties under section 149 of the Equality Act 2010. Statistical analysis of the potential impact of the proposals on people with the protected characteristics has informed high-level decision-making so far. As we obtain further local, site-specific information we will ensure any issues identified are also taken fully into consideration when the final decisions are made.</p><p> </p><p>Subject to further consideration of the proposal we hope to relocate all 31 staff and services from the current East Ham Jobcentre to Barking where we will continue to offer the same level of service to customers and claimants.</p><p> </p><p>The new site at Barking is 1.6 miles from the existing site and Jobcentre Plus is able to reimburse travel costs for those claiming Jobseekers’ Allowance or the equivalent claimants in Universal Credit for any attendance above their fortnightly signing appointment. In addition, those claiming Employment and Support Allowance and Income Support are not generally required to attend their local Jobcentre regularly</p><p> </p><p>In addition, our merged Jobcentres will continue to offer internet access to support claimants and we are working with local authorities as part of our ongoing partnership to improve digital access and capability.</p><p> </p><p>Where we are proposing to close a jobcentre we are taking all possible precautions to minimise disruption for customers, and vulnerable people will receive home visits and have the opportunity to make postal claims.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-03-20T17:44:26.82Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711099/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711099/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711099/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-03-14","Jobcentres: East Ham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of the closure of East Ham Jobcentre Plus on people in the local area trying to find work.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","67870"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711100","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-22","<p>There are now 88 Contract managers.</p><p> </p><p>The Pay grade breakdown is as follows:</p><p> </p><p>Executive Officer (EO) – 2</p><p> </p><p>Higher Executive Officer (HEO) – 22</p><p> </p><p>Senior Executive Officer (SEO) – 33</p><p> </p><p>Grade 7 – 28</p><p> </p><p>Grade 6 – 3</p>","Romsey and Southampton North","Caroline Nokes",,"2017-03-22T12:19:48.8Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711100/answer","Biography information for Caroline Nokes","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711100/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711100/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-03-14","Department for Work and Pensions: Pay","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, pursuant to the Answer of 24 February 2017 to Question 65535, on procurement, at what pay grades the 83 contract managers are employed.","false","Biography information for Jon Trickett","Hemsworth","Jon Trickett","67879"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711101","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-22","<p>We have sought to to minimise the impact on claimants travel as far as possible. The new site at Barking is 1.6 miles from the existing site and Jobcentre Plus is able to reimburse travel costs for those claiming Jobseekers’ Allowance or the equivalent claimants in Universal Credit for any attendance above their fortnightly signing appointment. In addition, those claiming Employment and Support Allowance and Income Support are not generally required to attend their local Jobcentre regularly.</p><p> </p><p>Throughout our planning we calculated distances and journey times to Barking using a variety of methods to ensure accuracy, including online tools and timetables, information collected on local public transport routes, and input and scrutiny from local DWP staff and management. Rather than assess the travel time from customers’ homes to their current and proposed new Jobcentre, we have focused instead on the distances between existing and proposed Jobcentre locations to help customers better understand any differences in distance. This is to reflect the fact that people who travel to the Jobcentre will use whichever type of transport suits their personal circumstances, they may not be starting their journey from their home, and not all those who use our services are claimants.</p><p> </p><p>In addition, throughout the development of these proposals, the department has been mindful of the impact on staff and customers as part of its duties under section 149 of the Equality Act 2010. Statistical analysis of the potential impact of the proposals on people with the protected characteristics has informed high-level decision-making so far. As we obtain further local, site-specific information we will ensure any issues identified are also taken fully into consideration when the final decisions are made.</p><p> </p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-03-22T12:10:59.803Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711101/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711101/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711101/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-03-14","Jobcentres: East Ham","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, what assessment his Department has made of the effect of increased journey times and travel costs for people currently using East Ham jobcentre of its closure.","false","Biography information for Stephen Timms","East Ham","Stephen Timms","67859"
"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711102","Department for Work and Pensions","false","2017-03-20","<p>In 2014/15 DWP closed 17 jobcentres, of which 4 were not relocated or co-located; and in 2015/16 closed 16 of which 6 were not relocated or co-located.</p>","East Hampshire","Damian Hinds",,"2017-03-20T17:51:14.243Z","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711102/answer","Biography information for Mr Damian Hinds","http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711102/answer",,,,,"http://data.parliament.uk/resources/711102/answer",,,,,"29","Work and Pensions","Work and Pensions","2017-03-14","Jobcentres: Closures","1","House of Commons","To ask the Secretary of State for Work and Pensions, how many jobcentres were closed in (a) 2014-15 and (b) 2015-16.","false","Biography information for Yasmin Qureshi","Bolton South East","Yasmin Qureshi","67893"
